    Class Description
    AbstractMenus
    The AbstractMenus class is an abstract class that houses common methods to all menus like prompting for the date, etc...
    AbstractPortfolioTest<T extends SimpleStockPortfolio>
    Abstract test class for portfolios.
    AbstractStockManagerTest<T extends SimpleStockManager>
    The AbstractStockManagerTest class represent tests common to Advanced and Simple StockManagers.
    AdvancedPortfolioMenu
    The AdvancedPortfolioMenu class extends the functionality of the SimplePortfolioMenu class to add support for the inputs that are need for the updated portfolio functionality.
    AdvancedStock
    the AdvancedStock class represents a stock with additional functionality.
    AdvancedStock.Transaction
    The static inner class Transaction represents a simple stock transaction, keeping track of the number of shares (+ if bought, - if sold), the date of the transaction, and the total value of the transaction (the pricePaid field tracks the entry price that the user paid to buy the stock, it is not currently used for any functionality but could be used later to track cost basis vs total portfolio value).
    AdvancedStockController
    The AdvancedStockController class is the new controller that supports upgraded functionality over the SimpleStockController.
    AdvancedStockManager
    The AdvancedStockManager is the updated model that extends the SimpleStockManager with new functionality for portfolios.
    AdvancedStockManagerTest
    Tests for advanced version of model.
    AdvancedStockPortfolio
    The AdvancedStockPortfolio class extends the functionality of the original SimpleStockPortfolio implementation to include the new functions (i.e.
    AdvancedStockPortfolioTest
    Tests for advanced stock portfolios.
    AdvancedStockTest
    The StockTest class represent tests for Stock objects and associated methods.
    AdvancedTextStockView
    The AdvancedTextStockView extends the SimpleTextStockView and overrides the portfolioMenu method to show the user the new key-binds for advanced portfolio operations.
    AlphaVantageDataSource
    The stocks.AlphaVantageDataSource class represents the data source for the AlphaVantage API.
    AlphaVantageDataSourceTest
    The AlphaVantageDataSourceTest class represents tests for methods on AlphaVantageDataSource objects.
    BetterStock
    The BetterStock interface extends the functionality of the Stock interface to allow for the adjusting of stocks on a certain day.
    BetterStockManager
    The BetterStockManager interface extends the original model interface and adds additional functionality to adjust a portfolio on a specific day.
    BetterStockPortfolio
    The BetterStockPortfolio interface extends the functionality of the StockPortfolio interface allowing for the buying and selling of stock on a certain day.
    CSVSources
    The stocks.CSVSources class represents all Comma Separated Values input sources including web and local files.
    CSVSourcesTest
    The CSVSourcesTest class represents tests for methods on CSVSources objects.
    DailyStockData
    The stocks.DailyStockData class represents day-to-day stock data in the form of high, low, open, close, and volume values.
    DailyStockDataTest
    The DailyStockDataTest class represents tests for DailyStockData objects and associated methods.
    DateRange
    The DateRange enum represents standard date ranges like week, month, year, etc...
    DateRangeTest
    Tests for DateRange enum.
    GraphicsStockController
    The GraphicsStockController class is an implementation on the StockController interface that works for graphical user interfaces.
    GraphicsStockView
    The GraphicsStockView interface defines operations and methods for graphical user interfaces (views) for the stock program.
    InputInteraction
    Represents a user providing the program with an input.
    Interaction
    An interaction with the user consists of some input to send the program and some output to expect.
    LocalCSVDataSource
    The LocalCSVDataSource class represents a CSV stock data source from a local file.
    LocalCSVDataSourceTest
    The LocalCSVDataSourceTest class represents tests for methods on LocalCSVDataSource objects.
    Menus
    The Menus interface is used to help replace a long switch statement in the controller this is designed to be a helper system to the controller that handles user inputs for specific menus, i.e.
    MockTestsForOutputs
    Class to test outputs of program.
    PrintInteraction
    Represents the printing of a sequence of lines to output.
    SimpleGraphicsStockView
    The SimpleGraphicsStockView class in an implementation on the GraphicsStock view interface and handles to view output with a GUI.
    SimplePortfolioMenu
    The SimplePortfolioMenu handles the inputs for the existing simple functions.
    SimpleStock
    The stocks.Stock class represents basic information about a stock in a portfolio, including symbol, number of shares, and historical data.
    SimpleStockController
    Controller class that processes user input this SimpleStockController is outdated because it doesn't support the new functions, but it is still used to handle any unchanged functionality and the inputs that are used for that.
    SimpleStockManager
    The mvc.model.SimpleStockManager class is the model in the MVC architecture of this program.
    SimpleStockManagerTest
    The SimpleStockManagerTest class represent test for the model and the model's methods.
    SimpleStockMenu
    The SimpleStockMenu support the inputs for basic stock functions like gain/loss, moving avg, crossovers.
    SimpleStockPortfolio
    The portfolios.SimpleStockPortfolio represent a regular, simplified stock portfolio with limited operations.
    SimpleStockPortfolioTest
    The SimpleStockPortfolioTest class represents tests for methods on SimpleStockPortfolio objects.
    SimpleStockTest
    The StockTest class represent tests for Stock objects and associated methods.
    SimpleTextStockView
    The mvc.view.TextStockView class represent the view, in the MVC architecture of this program.
    Stock
    The stock interface represents stock objects that are able to track their own number of shares, historical data and identity (ticker).
    StockController
    The StockController interface represents the handling of inputs to the stock program via the controller the StockController interface has two implementations that coexist, the Simple and Advanced controllers, the advanced controller class adds support for the new inputs while delegating any existing inputs to the simple controller.
    StockData
    The stocks.StockData interface represents different forms of stocks.Stock data and operations for that data.
    StockDataSource
    The stocks.StockDataSource interface represents different types of data sources for reporting stock information and methods to retrieve the data.
    StockManager
    The mvc.model.StockManager interface represents operations on stocks and is the interface that houses the methods for the model of this application.
    StockPortfolio
    The portfolios.StockPortfolio interface represent operations on a portfolio of stocks, allowing for the addition and removal of stocks as well as the calculation of total value on a given day.
    StockProgram
    Method to run the Stock program.
    TextStockView
    The TextStockView interface represents the handling of displaying results, menus, any other messages to the user/system.
